intro: Mitrephora collinsiae, commonly known as Collins' mitrephora, is a flowering plant native to the rainforests of Queensland, Australia. It belongs to the Anacardiaceae family, which includes cashew and poison ivy. The plant is characterized by its compound leaves and small, fragrant white flowers that bloom in clusters. It produces small, round fruits that are typically green when mature. Due to its limited distribution and habitat specificity, it is considered a rare and ecologically significant species.
